The global gluten-free products market can be segmented based on product type, distribution channel, end user, and region. In terms of product type, the market is categorized into breads & bakery products, snacks & ready-to-eat (RTE) products, pasta & rice, and others. The distribution channels for gluten-free products include online retail and offline retail. The end users for these products can be households or the food service industry. Geographically, the market is divided into North America, Europe, Asia Pacific, Latin America, and the Middle East & Africa.

